2.1.3 NCHRP REPORT 505 (2003) In NCHRP Report 505, the research team reviewed the range of dimensions and performance characteristics of trucks currently used on U.S. highways and predicted how these characteristics may change in response to current political, economic, and technological trends. The objective of this research is to evaluate whether the proposed geometric design (Table 2.1) in AASHTO Green Book (2001) was capable of accommodating heavy trucks. The evaluation of the recommendation table in Green Book, was conducted using the truck speed profile model (TSPM) to determine the weight-to-power ratios implied by the design values. Table 2.3 shows the maximum weight-to-power ratio of a truck capable of achieving the given conditions as specified in Table 2.1, assuming a 0 percent grade.
